{
  "stem": "1858.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was-- you know, there were long, gray barracks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were assigned about 30 girls to a room.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We slept on bunk beds.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were given a straw sack that served as a mattress, a pillow, a blanket.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "All our clothing was taken away from us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were given a uniform with a number.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the day that I entered the concentration camp, all my earthly possessions were taken away from me, even the very last-- my name.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I just became a number among so many other numbers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I cannot describe to you the feeling what it is when even your name no longer is yours, when you are just a number among so many other numbers.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Our food consisted of a slice of dark bread, a cup of black coffee, a bowl of watery soup.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And on that nourishment, we had to sustain ourselves while working 12-hour shifts.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At first, my sisters went for the rations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they asked that they give them one piece of bread for all three of us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had a reason for doing that until I discovered what they were doing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They tried to give me a little bit more bread than they had.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when I found out, then I asked for separate rations because I didn't want them-- although I was very hungry, I knew that they were just as hungry.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I did no longer want them to share with me and give up of their food.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I arrived in the camp, my sisters were at work.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, one of my sisters heard from the girls that just came for the new shift that arrived in the factory-- she heard from them that a girl by the name of Zaks arrived in the camp.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
